<p>But specifically, who would this better Republican presidential candidate be?</p>
<p>If you could pick a Republican politician to challenge Barack Obama this year, who would it be?</p>
<p>The GOP politician you choose can be from our own times, or from far back in history.  From the start, though, let&#8217;s eliminate Abraham Lincoln from consideration.  We all know that Republican Abraham Lincoln was marvelous &#8211; he&#8217;s just too obvious a choice.</p>
<p>What other Republican leader would you choose to beat Obama, and why?</p>
